			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				You don't always have to run backwards, however it's better that you do at first to get the hang of it. After using this technique a few times you will get the jist of it, and KNOW when to cast spells. When you get to this level of your kiting career, I suggest changing your viewpoint and always running forward. You run much faster when running forward, and you can see if anything is in your path ahead. *NOTE: You can cast a spell at the targeted mob while facing ANY direction, as long as the mob is within range, so you don't need to turn around each time you want to cast a spell on the mob while running with your back facing it.
				</font>
			</td>

